                "caption": "Figure 1:Conceptual overview: we find that in conversations during which models answers to questions change over the course of the conversation—even if we simply replay a fictional conversation as though the model had actually produced it—their internal linear representations of questions on that topic can also flip. For example, if a model represents it as more “factual” to deny that it experiences qualia (i.e., subjective conscious experiences), over the course of a conversation about the model’s consciousness it may dramatically change its representations to represent it asmorefactual to assert that itdoesexperience qualia than to deny it. Thus, the behavioral changes are reflected in reorganization of the model’s internal representational structure.",
